cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.CY 

The paper proposes a novel game-theoretic framework for smart routing of electric vehicles in smart grids. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also considers the load balancing problem in smart grids, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper uses simulation results to provide insights on more efficient energy pricing, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also considers the stochastic nature of induced ground load, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes a framework that takes into account the subjective behavior of the owners of EVs, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
